en_182675_0	The Department of Meteorology says that showers or thundershowers will occur in Western, Sabaragamuwa and Central provinces and in Galle and Matara districts today (Feb. 02).
en_182675_1	A few showers may occur in Uva province and in the Batticaloa, Hambantota and Ampara districts, it says.
en_182675_2	Moreover, the Department says that fairly heavy falls (about 75mm) can be expected at some places in the Nuwara-Eliya, Ratnapura and Kegalle districts.
en_182675_3	There may be temporary localized strong winds during thundershowers and the general public is requested to take adequate precautions to minimize damages caused by lightning activity.
